==Hebrew==

===Etymology===
Apparently from {{term|יד||hand|lang=he|sc=Hebr|tr=yad}}; literally, perhaps conveying the notion of being [[hand in hand]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Modern Israeli}} {{IPA|/jaˈdid/|lang=he}}

===Noun===
{{he-noun|wv=יָדִיד|tr=yadíd|g=m|cons=ידיד|conswv=יְדִיד|pl=ידידים|plwv=יְדִידִים|f=ידידה|fw=יְדִידָה}}

# A (male) platonic [[friend]].

====Usage notes====
* While the synonym {{term|lang=he|חבר|sc=Hebr|tr=khavér}} is more common in Modern Hebrew, it is ambiguous between a platonic friend and a romantic one; {{lang|he|יָדִיד}} is therefore often used to avoid this ambiguity.

